{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idcf5fb51f-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0","identifier":"/us/usc/t48/s731c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"731c"},"text":"§ 731c.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Submission of sections 731b to 731e of this title to people of Puerto Rico for referendum; convening of constitutional convention; requisites of constitution","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Sections 731b to 731e of this title shall be submitted to the qualified voters of Puerto Rico for acceptance or rejection through an island-wide referendum to be held in accordance with the laws of Puerto Rico. Upon the approval of said sections, by a majority of the voters participating in such referendum, the Legislature of Puerto Rico is authorized to call a constitutional convention to draft a constitution for the said island of Puerto Rico. The said constitution shall provide a republican form of government and shall include a bill of rights.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idcf5fb520-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-07-03/ch446/s2"},"text":"July 3, 1950, ch. 446, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/319"},"text":"64 Stat. 319","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idcf5fb521-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcf5fb522-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idcf5fb523-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was not enacted as part of the Puerto Rican Federal Relations Act which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idcf5fb524-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idcf5fb525-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Constitutional Convention","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A constitutional convention to draft a constitution for the island of Puerto Rico convened in San Juan on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1951-09-17"},"text":"Sept. 17, 1951","children":[],"tail":", and concluded its deliberations on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1952-02-06"},"text":"Feb. 6, 1952","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idcf5fb526-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Referendum","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1950-07-03"},"text":"July 3, 1950","children":[],"tail":", which enacted sections 731b to 731e of this title, was submitted to the qualified voters of Puerto Rico through an island-wide referendum held on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1951-06-04"},"text":"June 4, 1951","children":[],"tail":", and approved."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
